<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1422,1771]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1458,1483]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description.</emphasis>
Stolonal colonies, a filiform hydrorhiza giving rise to small hydrothecae on short pedicels (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1333,224,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[221,1362,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Modeeria rotunda (Quoy &amp; Gaimard, 1827): A, hydrotheca; B, basal part of hydrotheca showing diaphragm (arrow). Stegolaria geniculata (Allman, 1888): C, hydrotheca (note geniculate arrangement); D, hydrotheca showing plicate operculum; E, basal part of hydrotheca showing diaphragm (arrow); F, detail of distal part of hydrotheca. Stegopoma plicatile (M. Sars, 1863): G, adnate hydrotheca; H, free hydrotheca. Scale bars: Scale bars: 200 µm (A, C-D, G-H), 100 µm (B, E – F)," httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1044780/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Hydrotheca tubiform, with basal circular diaphragm (
<figureCitation box="[806,894,1494,1519]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1333,224,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[221,1362,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Modeeria rotunda (Quoy &amp; Gaimard, 1827): A, hydrotheca; B, basal part of hydrotheca showing diaphragm (arrow). Stegolaria geniculata (Allman, 1888): C, hydrotheca (note geniculate arrangement); D, hydrotheca showing plicate operculum; E, basal part of hydrotheca showing diaphragm (arrow); F, detail of distal part of hydrotheca. Stegopoma plicatile (M. Sars, 1863): G, adnate hydrotheca; H, free hydrotheca. Scale bars: Scale bars: 200 µm (A, C-D, G-H), 100 µm (B, E – F)," httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1044780/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Hydrothecal rim uneven, with two large cusps, separated by two large embayments (
<figureCitation box="[567,657,1530,1555]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1333,224,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[221,1362,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Modeeria rotunda (Quoy &amp; Gaimard, 1827): A, hydrotheca; B, basal part of hydrotheca showing diaphragm (arrow). Stegolaria geniculata (Allman, 1888): C, hydrotheca (note geniculate arrangement); D, hydrotheca showing plicate operculum; E, basal part of hydrotheca showing diaphragm (arrow); F, detail of distal part of hydrotheca. Stegopoma plicatile (M. Sars, 1863): G, adnate hydrotheca; H, free hydrotheca. Scale bars: Scale bars: 200 µm (A, C-D, G-H), 100 µm (B, E – F)," httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1044780/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Operculum composed of two semi-circular, pleated valves, attached to rim embayments and closing as a roof.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1422,1771]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Measurements (in µm). 
<emphasis box="[467,598,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Hydrotheca</emphasis>
: diameter at aperture 220–230; height, up to diaphragm 730–800, diameter at diaphragm 80–100, length of pedicel 100.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1422,1771]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,503,1674,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Ecology and distribution.</emphasis>
Eurybathic species, found at depths from 0.5 (
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia" box="[1032,1304,1675,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Garcia Carrascosa, A. M. (1981) Hidrozoos tecados (Hydrozoa Calyptoblastea) del litoral mediterraneo espanol: faunistica, ecologia, bionomia bentonica y biogeografia. Dissertation, University of Valencia, Valencia, 464 pp." type="book" year="1981">García Carrascosa 1981</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<quantity box="[1350,1436,1675,1699]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.214" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="1214.0">1214 m</quantity>
(Schuchert 2001); the present material was collected from the Porcupine Seabight at 
<quantity box="[1101,1174,1710,1735]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="150.0">150 m</quantity>
, on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lamouroux" baseAuthorityYear="1821" box="[1220,1408,1710,1735]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sertulariidae" genus="Sertularella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="gayi">
<emphasis box="[1220,1408,1710,1735]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sertularella gayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1422,1771]" box="[199,1006,1746,1771]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Circumglobal from boreal to tropical waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Vervoort" box="[707,994,1747,1771]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Vervoort, W. &amp; Watson, J. E. (2003) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand. Leptothecata (Cnidaria: Hydrozoa) (Thecate Hydroids). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir, 119, 1 - 538." type="journal article" year="2003">Vervoort &amp; Watson 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
